The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 June is 42,478 (4,916.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 June, there were 176 new confirmed cases (20.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 May, there were 65 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 171% (111 extra cases).
